<h2>How does a Web Application Work?</h2>
A web app mainly requires 3 elements to function properly which include a web server tohandle all the requests from the client, an application server to execute allthe tasks requested, and also a database to store the information.
<ul role="list">
 	<li>Here the user will connect to the Internet and will request a web server through the application's user interface.</li>
 	<li>The web server will process the request and send it to the appropriate web app server</li>
 	<li>The web application server will perform the task and generate results of the required data</li>
 	<li>The web app server will send back the information to the web server</li>
 	<li>The web server will send the requested information to the client's device such as a laptop, or mobile phone</li>
</ul>
<h2>How does a Web Application Work?</h2>
